U.S. Cotton Planting Will Plunge Next Year, Informa Says

-- B y   J e f f   W i l s o n
-- 
2011-09-23T15:50:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/u-s-cotton-planting-will-plunge-next-year-informa-says.html
U.S. cotton planting probably will
plunge to 11.968 million acres next year, compared with 14.72
million that the government estimated this year,  Memphis ,
Tennessee-based researcher Informa Economics Inc. said today in
a report to clients.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Wilson in Chicago at 
 jwilson29@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net . 